  "texts": [
    "As previously established, this operation performs matrix multiplication between V and the vector encoded on the second register.",
    "Since the k th element of the vector V x j can be written as q V kq X jq, we get:j A ij |e j ⟩ |Vx j ⟩ = j A ij |e j ⟩ k ( q V kq X jq) |e k ⟩ = k j A ij ( q V kq X jq) |e j ⟩ |e k ⟩(3)Since y i = j A ij Vx j, its k th element can be written y ik = j A ij ( q V kq X jq).",
    "Therefore, the quantum state at the end of the circuit can be written as |y i ⟩ = k y ik |ϕ k ⟩ |e k ⟩ for some normalised states |ϕ k ⟩.",
    "Performing tomography on the second register generates the output vector y i.This circuit is a more direct method to compute each y i.",
    "Each y i uses a different A i in the first part of the circuit."
